column33:
*Description*

When the backend returns a {{429 Too Many Requests}} response (triggered by Nginx rate limiting), the frontend currently shows a generic error or no message at all. Users have no indication that they are being rate limited and should wait before retrying.

Error handling for 429 responses should be implemented at the API client layer with a clear, user-friendly notification.

*Acceptance Criteria:*

* -Identify which API clients are used in the frontend and which need 429 handling-
* -Add a {{rate_limit}} translation key to the error dictionary in all supported languages-
* -Handle 429 responses in the Axios client (REST endpoints)-
* -Handle 429 responses in the Apollo client (GraphQL endpoints)-
* -Verify that a 429 response from any endpoint triggers a user-facing notification with the correct message-

*Deliverables*

!image-20260526-161011.png|width=682,alt="image-20260526-161011.png"!

{code:javascript}const token = localStorage.getItem('RaStore.authToken');
const iv = setInterval(() => {
    for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
        fetch('/graphql/information', {
            method: 'POST',
            headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json', 'Authorization': Bearer ${token} },
            body: JSON.stringify({ query: '{ __typename }' }),
        });
    }
}, 50); 

setTimeout(() => clearInterval(iv), 15000);{code}

